Publications

   Our of the main goals of the SMILE group is to understand the process
   of species diversification, using three different approaches:

   1. A lineage-based approach enabling the inference of diversification
   processes from phylogenies;

   2. An individual-based approach based on the modeling of either
   population genetics or ecological interactions in the speciation
   process, or both;

   3. Mathematical studies linking the former approach to the latter one
   by means of limit theorems (separation of timescales, invariance
   principles, dimension reduction…).

   ...See the whole list of publications here

